Defendant Daniel George Voss in court with attorney Martin Jarvis.  John Martin Yackel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Also has 15 CM 132 and 15 CM 21.   State recites plea agreement: 15 CM 21 - plead to count 3 counts 1 DRI and 2 dismissed - 15 CM 132 plead to count 3 and counts 1 and 2 DRI - 15 CF 32 plead 1st 5 charges amended to misd. thefts and balance of counts would be DRI / jt. recommendation sentence w/held probation 3 years - 72 days county jail (15 CF 32)  - rest. L&M $237.97  (15 CM 132) - $78.00 Julie Voss restitution - AODA and follow thru - any conditions DOC may impose including any residential or impatient treatment.  Atty Jarvis agrees with addition operate m/v w/o owners consent would be dismissed out right makes further stmt as to the restitution by his mother Julie Voss.  Court questions defendant as to plea questionnaire. Stipulate to probable cause portion of information to take pleas.   Defendant entered plea of NC to count 3 in 15 CM 21 / 15 CM 132 count 3 and 15 CF 32 counts 1 thru 5.  Court finds defendant guilty count 3 15 CM 21, count 3 15 CM 132 and counts 1 thru 5 in 15 CF 32 / count 2 in 15 CM 21 is dismissed and count 1 is dismissed and read in along with counts 1 and 2 in 15 cm 132 .  State argues sentencing. Court questions Ms. Voss as to whether she would like to address the court.  Ms. Voss addressed the Court.   Atty Jarvis argues sentencing 72 days credit and is a jt. recommendation.  Court questions Atty Jarvis re: jail credit.  Atty Jarvis believes he did the 72 days on 15 CM 132 rather.  Court questions Atty Yackel.  State makes stmt.  Court questions Atty Jarvis.  Court questions the defendant.
